<doc id="613456" wikidata="Q1850957" url="?curid=613456" title="Agapanthoideae">
<text>Agapanthoideae is a monotypic subfamily of monocot flowering plants in the family Amaryllidaceae, order Asparagales. It is one of three subfamilies of Amaryllidaceae. It was formerly treated as a separate family, Agapanthaceae. The subfamily name is derived from the generic name of the type genus, &quot;Agapanthus&quot;.

Its sole genus, &quot;Agapanthus&quot;, is endemic to South Africa.

