<doc id="613521" wikidata="Q1300595" url="?curid=613521" title="Krishnamurti">
<text>( ) is a South Indian name. It has several variants.

==Variants==
Some forms separate the name elements , e.g. .
English language renditions generally follow corresponding variations of the name in regional Indian languages.
The following is a non-exhaustive list.
==Etymology and usage==
It is a compound of Sanskrit origin, derived from the Hindu deity Krishna and the term murti (form), meaning &quot;in the form (or image) of Krishna&quot;. In regional Indian naming conventions it is usually a given name, but it may also be a family name. In other cases it may be westernized as a surname.

==People==
Non-Indian nationality is when known. 

